verses.verse: O come, let vs synge vnto the Lord, let vs hertely reioyse in the strength of our saluacion.
Let vs come before his presence wt thankesgeuynge, & shewe oure selfe glad in hym wt psalmes.
For the Lorde is a great God, & a great kynge aboue all goddes.
In his hande are all the corners of the earth, & the strength of the hylles is his also.
The see is hys, and he made it, & his handes prepared the drye lande.
O come, let vs worshyppe & fall downe, and knele before the Lord oure maker.
For he is oure God: and we are the people of his pasture, and the shepe of his handes.
To daye yf ye will heare his voyce, harden not your hertes, as in the prouokacion & as in the daye of temptacion in the wildernes.
When youre fathers tempted me, proued me, and saw my workes.
Fourty yeares long was I greued with that generacion, & sayd: it is a people that do erre in theyr hertes: for they haue not knowen my wayes.
Unto whom I sware in my wrath that they shulde not enter in to my rest.
